 <text id="A4098T">
  <front id="d2">
   <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
    <p>Hotchkiss writes a brief note to his wife, telling her the location of the army.</p>
   </div1>
  </front>

  <body id="d4">
   <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
    <head>
     <name type="recipient">Sara A. Hotchkiss</name>
    </head>

    <opener>
     <dateline>
      <date value="1864-10-08">Oct 8<hi rend="super">th</hi> 1864</date>
      <name type="place">New Market Va --</name>
     </dateline>
     <salute>My Dear Sara</salute>
    </opener>

    <p>We got here yesterday &amp; are resting today -- the enemy has gone on down the Valley
     they did a great deal of burning -- I am very <orig reg="tired">tirde</orig> -- it is really
     cold this morning -- Keep my coat until I send for it -- The news from Missouri &amp;
     Georgia is very cheering -- I send you a piece of a Broome <abbr expan="County">Co.</abbr>
     paper Send it to Nelson -- the Courier is going &amp; I can only say blessings on you all
     &amp; love for you -- Write me often -- I suppose we shall go on -- </p>

    <closer>
     <salute>Your <abbr expan="Affectionate">Aff</abbr> husband</salute>
     <signed>Jed. Hotchkiss</signed>
    </closer>
   </div1>
  </body>
 </text>
